25/11/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- Macedonian Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski will meet with US Secretary of State Colin Powell and Vice President Dick Cheney on Tuesday (25 November). 
He spent Monday in Detroit, where he met with members of the Macedonian diaspora. 
Crvenkovski urged them to support and invest in Macedonia, and opened a Macedonian consular office in the city. 
The prime minister, accompanied by Deputy Prime Minister Musa Xhaferri and Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva, has also met with IMF and World Bank representatives during his visit.
In other news, the Canadian government announced it would close its consular office in Skopje at the end of February, saying its provisional mandate has been fulfilled. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 25/11/03; MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 24/11/03)
